authorized rapid intake, forced quarantines, @@rsuspension of lineage
appeals@@N. "Temporary" appears forty-three times across the Mandate
instruments. Not once does a sunset date accompany it.

Temporary became permanent. What had been a frontier court became an
@@rintake machine@@N. Bodies processed doubling, tripling. Requisitions
for salt, preservative, ward-iron -- each @@dapproved, stamped,
witnessed, sealed@@N by our own clerks.

When plague receded, no authority agreed on rollback. The @@rLast Bell
Crisis@@N saw three contradictory decrees rung in one night: amnesty,
lockdown, requisition. The city calcified into hostile systems, each
invoking @@yMidgaard's authorization@@N.

The @@dBlight Hydrology Doctrine@@N records our failure. Alchemical
disposal entered runoff channels. Crypts flooded from below. The
blight is @@rinfrastructure memory@@N -- ours, remembering our decisions.

Five factions invoke law; none can establish legitimacy. The
@@WOathbound March@@N executing our obsolete orders. The @@rCrimson
Household@@N claiming bloodline under our charter. The @@dBinder
Collegium@@N treating souls as ledger entries in our format. The
@@rGallows Syndicate@@N who turned sentence infrastructure into economy.
The @@eFen-Adapted Remnants@@N beyond governance entirely.

The Reckoning faction has compiled a @@dcomplete chain of
authorization@@N -- every requisition approved, every sunset clause
omitted. They want it read in the public square.

Shadowmere is what happens when lawful systems become @@rpredatory
under emergency powers without sunset@@N. The orders bear our seal.
This is the file the Reckoning wants opened and the Continuity wants
@@dsealed and administratively resolved@@N. The Bureau @@rmakes no
